The paper discusses the connection between generative adversarial networks (GANs), inverse reinforcement learning (IRL), and energy-based models (EBMs). These topics are all related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that the paper likely belongs to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of GANs and IRL in computer vision (cs.CV) and control and reinforcement learning (cs.RO, cs.SY), which further supports these sub-categories as likely candidates. Finally, the paper also touches on the use of cost functions in machine learning (cs.AI), which is another possible sub-category.
